race.comment: GAMOLINA (6) missed the placings two starts back when resuming then ran a better race and finished 1.4 lengths away in fifth last time out over 1200m at Parkes. Well placed and there is no reason she cannot find winning ways. CHICKEN LEGS (2) was out of the money two runs back then again missed the frame last start over 1000m at this track when sixth. Has the class to figure prominently. LA PELAGO (1) was in the firing line on the turn with a sound second over 1108m at Port Macquarie. Hard to beat in this suitable race. POWERSTONE (5) was below her best last time, finishing sixth over 1000m at Gunnedah. Nicely placed to turn things around.
